Description:
The homepage of the site with nothing but two images;
the first image is a simple black sphere, whilst the 
other one is essentially the same but with a sitemap
and some effects. As soon as one hovers over the first
image, it renders itself invisible, thus showing the
image underneath. A simple, yet very effective usage of
a piece of a code I found here:
http://css3.bradshawenterprises.com/cfimg/

There's a menu with four categories (technically three)
on the top. The access to the homepage (though quite
unnecessary) is provided by the ©Nerozette link in the
lower left corner of the page.

All of the images were formerly something like
http://placekitten.com/200/200, but I downloaded them
just to make sure.
-->
